      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When multiple planets align, it's not a literal gathering, but rather a coincidence in their positions due to their orbital paths. As you move through your orbit, your angle of view changes, making some alignments more noticeable from certain locations. Think of it like trying to fit a puzzle piece – there's only one way to make one piece fit, but the shape and surroundings change depending on the angle. These alignments are often referred to as \"syzygies\" or \"mean anomaly\" events, and their visibility depends on Earth's position relative to the orbits of the planets involved.",
